@startuml fig-http-caching-304
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title HTTP Caching — Conditional Requests and 304 Not Modified

participant "Browser\n(cache)" as B #FFE0B2
participant "Server" as S #C8E6C9

== First Request — Full Response ==

B -> S : GET /data.json
S -[#43A047]-> B : 200 OK\nLast-Modified: Mon, 10 Feb 2025\nCache-Control: max-age=60\n\n{...payload...}

note right of B
  Browser stores the response
  and the Last-Modified date.
end note

|||
...60 seconds later (cache expired)...
|||

== Conditional Request — Cache Validation ==

B -> S : GET /data.json\nIf-Modified-Since: Mon, 10 Feb 2025

alt Resource unchanged
  S -[#43A047]-> B : 304 Not Modified\n(no body)
  note right of B : Browser uses cached copy
else Resource changed
  S -[#1565C0]-> B : 200 OK\nLast-Modified: Wed, 12 Feb 2025\n\n{...new payload...}
  note right of B : Browser replaces cached copy
end

legend right
  304 dramatically reduces bandwidth:
  the server confirms validity without
  retransmitting the full payload.
  Caches operate at browser, proxy and CDN layers.
endlegend
@enduml
